  "prompt": "What companies and startups use GitHub?",
  "response": "A vast array of companies and startups utilize GitHub for their development, collaboration, and version control needs. Some notable ones include:\n\n1. **Microsoft**: As the parent company of GitHub, Microsoft uses GitHub extensively across different projects and teams.\n   \n2. **Google**: Many Google open-source projects are hosted on GitHub, including TensorFlow and Kubernetes.\n   \n3. **Facebook**: Facebook uses GitHub for several open-source projects like React, React Native, and PyTorch.\n   \n4. **Netflix**: They host various projects related to cloud management and security.\n   \n5. **Airbnb**: Known for their commitment to open-source, Airbnb hosts projects like Lottie and Enzyme on GitHub.\n   \n6. **Uber**: The company shares some of its engineering tools and data visualization projects on GitHub.\n   \n7. **Twitter**: Twitter has several open-source projects on GitHub, including Bower and Heron.\n   \n8. **Spotify**: They contribute to and host various open-source projects on GitHub in the audio and machine learning domains.\n   \n9. **Shopify**: The company hosts a number of its open-source libraries and tools for commerce on GitHub.\n   \n10. **Red Hat**: As a significant contributor to open-source software, Red Hat utilizes GitHub for many of its projects.\n   \n11. **Automattic (WordPress)**: They host and contribute to multiple plugins and themes available to the WordPress community on GitHub.\n\nStartups also heavily rely on GitHub for its capabilities to streamline collaboration and development. Startups across various sectors, including fintech, health tech, edtech, and more, use GitHub as a central part of their tech stack, appreciating features like GitHub Actions for CI/CD, issues and pull requests for team collaboration, and GitHub Pages for hosting.\n\nGitHub is a staple for companies of all sizes due to its robust ecosystem and the vibrant community that surrounds it, facilitating both private and public software development.",
